Interface DataSetManipulator

All Known Implementing Classes:
BasicDataSetManipulator
public interface DataSetManipulator
Class that is used to perform various operations on DatSet object

  • Method Details

    • getStatistics

      java.util.Vector<Statistics> getStatistics​(DataSet dataSet, java.time.Instant from, java.time.Instant to) throws DataSetNotOpenedException
      Method that returns statistics for all fields in the dataset.
      Parameters:
      dataSet - Data set to get statistics from.
      from - Beginning of the time period for the statistics default - Instant.MIN.
      to - End of the time period of the statistics default - Instant.MIN.
      Returns:
      Vector of Statistics, each element represents different field
      Throws:
      DataSetNotOpenedException - if user tries to get statistics before successfully opening a dataset
      See Also:
      Statistics

    • getStatistics

      Statistics getStatistics​(DataSet dataSet, java.lang.String fieldName, java.time.Instant from, java.time.Instant to) throws NoFieldFoundException, DataSetNotOpenedException
      Method that returns statistics for selected field in the dataset. If param from is after param to, they are switched.
      Parameters:
      dataSet - Data set to get statistics from.
      fieldName - Name of the selected field.
      from - Beginning of the time period for the statistics default - Instant.MIN.
      to - End of the time period of the statistics default - Instant.MIN.
      Returns:
      Statistics for selected field and time period
      Throws:
      NoFieldFoundException - if there is no field with provided fieldName in the dataset
      DataSetNotOpenedException - if user tries to get statistics before successfully opening a dataset
      See Also:
      Statistics
